ired as models of neatness and accuracy."},{"number":2,"category":"literature","header":"A diffident poet with a trenchant pen","body":"A lifelong lover of poetry who studied law but was too shy to practice it, Welles instead wielded a busy pen for the press. His political essays were said to carry conviction to the reader and scathing rebuke to the corrupt politician."},{"number":3,"category":"death","header":"A fall from his wagon killed him","body":"Welles kept a hand in public affairs for half a century and rarely missed a term of court at Towanda. In 1866, getting down from his wagon, he was thrown heavily and died of his injuries."}],"sources":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"first_name":"Charles","last_name":"Welles","married_names":[],"display_name":"Charles Fisher Welles","middle_name":"Fisher","gender":"male","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1780699202/charleswelles_xh6spx.png","photo_notes":"Charles Fisher Welles (1789–1866), first prothonotary of Bradford County.","bio_blurb":"Bradford County's first prothonotary and clerk"},"military_service":[],"career":[{"role":"Prothonotary & Clerk of Courts","organization":"Bradford County PA","start_year":1812,"end_year":1818,"notes":"County's first."},{"role":"Farmer & real estate","organization":"Wyalusing, Pennsylvania","start_year":1822}],"slug":"charles-welles-1789"},"I01522":{"id":"I01522","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"gender":"female","birth":{"year":1788,"month":1,"day":21,"city":"Wilkes-Barre","state":"Pennsylvania","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1876,"month":3,"day":14,"city":"Wyalusing","state":"Pennsylvania","country":"United States"},"burial":{},"residence":{"city":"Wyalusing","state":"Pennsylvania","country":"United States"},"classification":{"is_thoma