ty years on the Luzerne County bench","body":"On the organization of Luzerne County, Hollenback was appointed an associate judge alongside Colonel Denison. He held the commission for nearly forty years, to the time of his death."}],"sources":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[{"type":"civic_peer","display_label":"fought at the Battle of Wyoming with William Hooker Smith","related_id":"H00320","link_text":"William Hooker Smith"},{"type":"civic_peer","display_label":"shared the Wyoming Valley frontier with Colonel John Spalding","related_id":"X03095","link_text":"Col. John Spalding"},{"type":"civic_peer","display_label":"Wyoming Valley settler beside General Simon Spalding","related_id":"X03106","link_text":"Gen. Simon Spalding"},{"type":"in_law","related_id":"T01809","display_label":"married his son John in 1805"}],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"first_name":"Matthias","last_name":"Hollenback","married_names":[],"display_name":"Matthias Hollenback","gender":"male","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1780699335/63611106_4b553759-e3f2-40a2-9a13-de71f1ceb298_pgnlhv.jpg","photo_notes":"Judge Matthias Hollenback (1752–1829), Wyoming Valley merchant and jurist."},"military_service":[{"war":"American Revolutionary War","active_in_war":true,"rank":"Ensign; later Colonel of militia","notes":"An inhabitant of the Wilkes-Barre stockade by 1771. Commissioned ensign by Congress for the Westmoreland independent companies; fought at the Battle of Wyoming, July 3, 1778, escaped across the Susquehanna to Monocacy Island, then rode through the night to summon Capt. Simon Spalding's company and helped bury the slain.","war_id":"WAR004"}],"career":[{"role":"Merchant","organization":"Susquehanna Valley stores","notes":"Wilkes-Barre to the Genesee."},{"role":"Associate Judge","organization":"Luzerne County, Pennsylvania","start_year":1787,"notes"